	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65021623"><p>Edinburgh is a great city, but the public transport is a mess.</p><p><div class="quote"><p>I would be completely unsurprised to learn that the origin and destination stops and timings weren't integrated into other forms of public transport</p></div><p>Almost certainly right. Also, in Edinburgh, you have various bus companies, but your ticket is only valid for one company. So if you need to change buses, you have to buy multiple tickets. This is also the city that nearly bankrupted itself installing a tram running from the airport to downtown, even though there was a perfectly good bus route doing the same thing. The tram isn't faster, and it is more expensive.</p></div>
